notes.note:
Customer email. Long email about how he partnered buying the vehicle and his partner stopped paying, etc. 
He wanted to start a claim for an electrical issue and brake problems. I explained the warranty coverage which does not cover brakes or electrical. If he wished, I referred to Ultimate Auto. A.H.

Thank you for your email.
I'm sorry for the situation in which you find yourself.
To make a claim against the warranty, the vehicle must go to a Canada General authorized repair facility.
In Mississauga we use:
Ultimate Auto Centre
1773 Mattawa Ave.
Mississauga
Phone - 905-272-9379

That being said, the warranty on this vehicle is a Principal Warranty which covers the Powertrain.
The coverage is for the internally lubricated parts of the engine, transmission, differential and transfer case, as listed on the warranty. There is no coverage for electrical or brake components.

If you do have troubles that may be related to the warranty coverage, please contact Ultimate Auto where they will initiate a claim on your behalf.

Sincerely,
Adam Halko
Claims Manager

Either way we have no obligation to this contract once this repair is done as the contract is now expired. M.P.

notes.note:
Good evening Ken, thank you for your previous email with the estimate for the replacement of the cylinder head gasket and associated hardware on Mr. Ross' Accent. Please be advised, any diagnostic fees, shop supplies, fluids, spark plugs, exhaust components (including gaskets) and environmental fees are not covered and are therefore the responsibility of the customer. Additionally, our Mitchell Labour Guide calls for 7.2 hours for the replacement of the head gasket, so this is the maximum we will be able to authorize. Finally, the customer has a $100 deductible + tax. 

As you have indicated over the phone during some of our previous conversations and on the estimate, the customer is also facing issues with the piston rings and cylinder walls within the engine being worn, allowing oil to seep into the combustion chamber and burn oil. You have suggested that he replace the engine with a used engine to hit two birds with one stone and correct the head gasket issue and the worn piston ring issue. That being said, the following authorized repair amount can be used towards either the replacement of the cylinder head, or the replacement of the current motor with a used motor instead. 

If the customer chooses to replace the motor with a used unit, the customer will be responsible for the balance of the repair above the authorized amount listed below.
